Description: Wall sherd of East Greek (South Ionian) pottery closed vessel; light orange clay with much silver mica; traces of cream slip on the outside; inscription cut on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.938)
